						               													<description>We're in the end of the 70's in Rapid Falls, a small town in South Dakota. An Air Force base, rotten motels and diners, beautiful crates, an Indian reserve and some remains from Western, nothing is missing ... A familiar universe enriched with the great mythologies of the time : ufo, sasquatch and ...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Rapid Falls, you will follow the adventures of two protagonists who oppose everything: Gwen, a nonviolent empathic medium and Jeffrey, a cynical, grumpy and disillusioned cop. Through their adventures, you will plunge into America of the seventies through their eyes and reactions. The tone is mature, the themes are sometimes a little dark or tragic, and some situations sadly ironic. The relationship between characters evolves over the course of investigations and narrative arcs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rapid Falls is a trans-media gaming project with a board, booklets, tokens and some digital game aids (MP3 audio of interrogations or PDF files for easy searching).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play? Put the board on the table and discover the city of Rapid Falls. Then, take your case an start your investigation. Browse the booklet to be given clue. Check for the driver's licence database to find people. Get tokens to unlock some informations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Will you try to go the fastest to the final issue? Or do you prefer to explore this world and maybe find its hidden secrets? It's up to you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
